<inglise> of 29 January 2001 derogating from Regulation (EC) No 2316/1999 laying down detailed rules for the application of Council Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999 with regard to set-aside as a result of the adverse weather conditions in some Community regions </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 180/2001, millega kehtestatakse erand m&auml;&auml;rusest (E&Uuml;) nr 2316/1999, milles s&auml;testatakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad seoses maa tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldamisega halbade ilmastikutingimuste t&otilde;ttu &uuml;henduse teatavates piirkondades 29. jaanuar 2001 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999 of 17 May 1999 establishing a support system for producers of certain arable crops(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1672/2000(2), and in particular Article 9 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 17. mai 1999. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999, millega kehtestatakse teatavate p&otilde;llukultuuride tootjatele toetuss&uuml;steem, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1672/2000, (2) eriti selle artiklit 9, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Eligibility for the area aid under the general scheme referred to in Article 2(3) of Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999 is subject to an obligation to set land aside. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud &uuml;ldkava alusel pindalatoetuse saamise tingimuseks on kohustus maa tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldada; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The detailed rules of application fixed by Commission Regulation (EC) No 2316/1999(3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2860/2000(4), stipulate that the set-aside period must begin no later than 15 January and that no agricultural production is authorised on the land set aside. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2316/1999, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2860/2000, (4) kehtestatud &uuml;ksikasjalikes rakenduseeskirjades s&auml;testatakse, et maa tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldamine peab algama hiljemalt 15. jaanuaril ja tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldatud maal ei ole lubatud mingisugune p&otilde;llumajanduslik tootmine; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) As a result of adverse weather conditions the producers in various regions of some Member States cannot harvest their crops, especially of potatoes, sugar beet, fodder beet, carrots and parsnips, before 15 January 2001, on lands to be set aside in the 2001/02 marketing year. Under the circumstances, and as an exceptional measure, where growers so request they should be authorised to harvest their crops no later than 28 February 2001 without this affecting recognition of the lands in question as properly set aside, provided that they prove that the applicable conditions have been complied with. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) halbade ilmastikutingimuste t&otilde;ttu ei saa m&otilde;nede liikmesriikide eri piirkondade tootjad koristada oma saaki, eriti kartulit, suhkrupeeti, s&ouml;&ouml;dapeeti, porgandit ja pastinaaki, 2001/02. turustusaastal tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldatavalt maalt enne 15. jaanuari 2001; neil asjaoludel tuleks erandliku abin&otilde;una anda tootjatele taotluse korral luba koristada oma saak hiljemalt 28. veebruaril 2001 ning tunnistada k&otilde;nealused alad n&otilde;uetekohaselt tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldatuks, kui tootja t&otilde;endab, et kohaldatavad tingimused on t&auml;idetud; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Cereals, </inglise>
<eesti> 4) k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las teraviljaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Where a producer, upon application to the competent authority of the Member State concerned, can prove that: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tootja suudab taotluse korral t&otilde;endada asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devale asutusele, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - harvesting could not take place before 15 January 2001 as a result of adverse weather conditions, </inglise>
<eesti> - saagikoristus ei saanud halbade ilmastikutingimuste t&otilde;ttu toimuda enne 15. jaanuari 2001, </eesti>
<inglise> - harvesting, where done, was done no later than 28 February 2001, or no later than 31 March 2001 in the case of potatoes and beet, </inglise>
<eesti> - saagikoristuse toimumise korral koristati saak hiljemalt 28. veebruaril 2001 v&otilde;i kartuli ja peedi puhul hiljemalt 31. m&auml;rtsil 2001, </eesti>
<inglise> - all the other conditions applying to set-aside land have been complied with, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;ik muud maa tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldamise suhtes kohaldatavad tingimused on t&auml;idetud, </eesti>
<inglise> the lands in question shall be considered, notwithstanding Article 19(2) and (3) of Regulation (EC) No 2316/1999, as properly set aside for the 2001/02 marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;sitatakse asjaomast maad 2001/02. turustusaastal n&otilde;uetekohaselt tootmisest k&otilde;rvaldatuna, olenemata m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2316/1999 artikli 19 l&otilde;igetest 2 ja 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 15 January 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rus kohaldatakse alates 15. jaanuarist 2001. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 29 January 2001. </inglise>
